{
  "title": "Abortive Phage Resistance Mechanism AbiZ Speeds the Lysis Clock To Cause Premature Lysis of Phage-Infected Lactococcus lactis",
  "summary": "The paper discusses several Lactococcus phages, primarily focusing on their interactions with the abortive infection system AbiZ encoded by plasmid pTR2030. Phage φ31 and related phages (φ31.1, φ31.2) show varying sensitivities to AbiZ, which causes premature lysis and reduces burst size. Other P335 group phages (ul36, ul37, Q30) also exhibit sensitivity to AbiZ, while 936 group phages (sk1, p2) and c2 group phage c2 are largely resistant. The study highlights the role of AbiZ in interacting with phage holin to induce early lysis.",
